Microsoft commonly categorizes cloud migration strategies into the "6 Rs":

* Rehost (Lift and Shift)
* Refactor
* Rearchitect
* Rebuild
* Replace
* Retire

Each strategy depends on business goals, application complexity, and modernization requirements.

For example, a legacy payroll application may initially be rehosted, while a customer-facing application may be rearchitected into microservices.

A real-life use case is organizations gradually modernizing applications instead of rewriting everything at once.

Understanding the 6 Rs helps organizations choose the most appropriate migration approach.
